Reasoning: The paper discusses online learning with logarithmic loss and regular parametric models, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of Bayesian prediction strategy with Jeffreys prior and sequential normalized maximum likelihood (SNML) also suggests a focus on statistical learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information theory (IT) in the discussion of SNML and exchangeability. Additionally, the use of exponential families and Fisher information suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI) and statistics (ST). Finally, the study of online learning and logarithmic loss may also fall under the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (DS).
